The Police Command in Kaduna yesterday said they arrested a suspected kidnapper and gunrunner in Zaria. Spokesman ASP Mohammad Jalige said that operatives, on Tuesday, arrested Rilwanu Abdullahi of Damari village in Birnin Gwari council with an AK47 rifle with 600 rounds of ammunition. Jalige said the suspect was seen in a suspicious manner around Madachi area of Zaria and on sighting the operatives, he attempted to escape but was chased and apprehended.   Lagos begins crackdown on Okada June 1     Gunmen kill four, set building ablaze in Ebonyi     Police arrest suspected abductors of Greenfield students    “A search carried out on his Volkswagen vehicle led to the recovery of the said rifle. “The suspect led detectives to another location where an additional Volkswagen car was recovered with the said number of live ammunition carefully concealed inside the fuel tank aimed at evading the eagle eyes of security operatives. “Despite all odds the police are not relenting in ensuring that no stone is left unturned in their resolve to reduce crime to the barest minimum,” the police spokesman said.